UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1470
1 AN ACT proposing an amendment to Section 145 of the Constitution of Kentucky
2 relating to persons entitled to vote.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of amending Section 145 of the Constitution of
5 Kentucky to prohibit persons adjudged mentally incompetent by a court from voting as
6 stated below?
7 Section 2. It is proposed that Section 145 of the Constitution of Kentucky be
8 amended to read as follows:
9 Every citizen of the United States of the age of eighteen years who has resided in
10 the state one year, and in the county six months, and the precinct in which he or she
11 offers to vote sixty days next preceding the election, shall be a voter in said precinct and
12 not elsewhere. No person who is not a citizen of the United States shall be allowed to
13 vote in this state. The following persons also shall not have the right to vote:
14 1. Persons convicted in any court of competent jurisdiction of treason, or felony,
15 or bribery in an election, or of such high misdemeanor as the General Assembly may
16 declare shall operate as an exclusion from the right of suffrage, but persons hereby
17 excluded may be restored to their civil rights by executive pardon.
18 2. Persons who, at the time of the election, are in confinement under the
19 judgment of a court for some penal offense.
20 3. Persons determined by a court of competent jurisdiction to be mentally
21 incompetent to vote, when that judicial determination has not been set aside[Idiots and
22 insane persons].
23 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
24 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
25 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and Sections 4 and 5
26 of this Act.
27 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
